longBusinessSummary: MMC Corporation Berhad, an investment holding company, engages in the utilities and infrastructure businesses in Malaysia. The company operates through Ports and Logistics, Energy and Utilities, Engineering, Airports, and Others segments. The company develops, constructs, operates, manages, and maintains ports, container and cruise terminals, and airports, as well as offers port facilities and other related services. It is also involved in the design and construction of sewage systems; operation, maintenance, and management of water treatment plants; civil engineering construction works; management of a distribution center with warehousing, storage, and other associated facilities; operation of rail cargo; dockyard operations; construction of stormwater management and road tunnel motorway; and property ownership, investment, and development businesses. In addition, the company provides warehouse and office space; cargo and container handling; freight forwarding; internal and external haulage; logistics; container repairs and maintenance; project management; engineering, construction, and professional services to the oil and gas and resources industries; rental of port premises and other ancillary services; and human resources and management services. Further, it generates electricity as an independent power producer; distributes natural gas to the non-power sector; develops, operates, and maintains 2,334 kilometers of natural gas distribution networks; engages in mining and mineral exploration activities; and offers waste water recycling technology. Additionally, MMC Corporation Berhad holds properties; and manages, operates, and maintains an airport. The company was founded in 1911 and is based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. MMC Corporation Berhad is a subsidiary of Seaport Terminal (Johore) Sdn Bhd.
